  "doc_id": "21475",
  "text": "The prevalence of drug use in adolescents was 56% in a survey involving secondary-school students in Germany [CITATION_1] and 70% in a study that analysed prescriptions made by general practitioners in New Zealand [CITATION_2] . According to the first survey, the drugs most commonly used by the adolescents were antipyretics (35% of the adolescents), cough and cold medicines (23%) and sex hormones and urologicals (13%) [CITATION_3] . In all, 28% of the prescriptions monitored in the second study were for respiratory system drugs, 23% for antinfectives and 10% for sex hormones and urologicals [CITATION_4] . ",
